PHNOM PENH, Dec. 7 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Prime Minister Samdech Techo Hun Sen will visit Myanmar on Jan. 7 and 8, his personal spokesman said here on Tuesday. Myanmar's foreign minister U Wunna Maung Lwin brought an invitation letter from Commander-in-Chief of Defence Services Sen-Gen Min Aung Hlaing, chairman of the State Administration Council of Myanmar, to Hun Sen on Tuesday morning, said Eang Sophalleth, a personal spokesman for the Cambodian prime minister. "Samdech Techo Hun Sen accepted the invitation and told His Excellency U Wunna Maung Lwin that he will visit Myanmar on Jan. 7 and 8, 2022," he said. U Wunna Maung Lwin is in Cambodia for a two-day visit. He arrived in Phnom Penh on Monday. Enditem